{{distinguish|text=the Indian historian of medieval India, [[Irfan Habib]]}} {{more citations needed|date=January 2018}} [[File:Prof. S. Irfan Habib.jpg|thumbnail]] '''Syed Irfan Habib''' (born 1953) is an Indian historian of science and a public intellectual. He held the [[Abul Kalam Azad]] Chair at the [[National University for Educational Planning and Administration]] (NUEPA), New Delhi during 2009-2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nuepa.org/new/Irfan_Habib.aspx|title=National University of Educational Planning and Administration - Maulana Abul Kalam Azad Chair|website=nuepa.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/edit-page/S-Irfan-Habib-Modern-science-can-be-pursued-by-any-believer/articleshow/17052707.cms|title=S Irfan Habib: Modern science can be pursued by any believer|author=|date=|work=The Times of India|accessdate=21 January 2016}}</ref> Before joining NUEPA, he was a scientist at the [[National Institute of Science, Technology and Development Studies]] (NISTADS), New Delhi.{{citation needed|date=August 2017}}
==Work== Habib's intellectual collaboration with [[Dhruv Raina]] has initiated the publication of a series of articles and books on social history of science in India. For the last ten years, Habib has been writing and speaking about Islam and the decline of critical imagination.{{citation needed|date=August 2017}} A book reflecting on this issue was published in 2012 called ''Jihad or Ijtihad'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=RWID1neRoucC&pg=PT83&dq=S+Irfan+habib+translation+Malayalam&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjJvJCUj-jLAhXXBY4KHdQzA7wQ6AEIGzAA#v=onepage&q=S+Irfan+habib+translation+Malayalam&f=false|title=Jihad Or Itjihad : Religious Orthodoxy And Modern Science In Contemporary India|first=S. Irfan|last=Habib|date=1 December 2013|publisher=Harper Collins|via=Google Books}}</ref> wherein he explores the critical traditions of Islamic scholarship in South Asia. An intellectual biography of [[Maulana Abul Kalam Azad]] locating him in the present day global Islamic context is forthcoming.{{citation needed|date=August 2017}}
Habib's work on [[Bhagat Singh]] and his comrades (''To Make the Deaf Hear: Ideology and Programme of Bhagat Singh and His Comrades'', 2007)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.threeessays.com/books/to-make-the-deaf-hear/|title=To Make the Deaf Hear: Ideology and Programme of Bhagat Singh and His Comrades - By S. Irfan Habib|publisher=}}</ref> established Bhagat Singh as a revolutionary ideologue of the Hindustan Socialist Republican Association. Until a few years ago{{when|date=January 2018}} he was remembered only as a martyr, while Habib's reading of Bhagat Singh's original writings and archival sources presented him as a thinker. [[K. N. Panikkar|K.N. Panikkar]] in his review of the book underscores this by stating, "Irfan Habib's account is a meticulously documented and analytical work which takes particular care to portray the political and intellectual evolution of Bhagat Singh as a revolutionary. The focus of this work is not on events, but on the ideological processes which enabled Bhagat Singh to espouse a revolutionary philosophy and a programme of political action".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-bookreview/Beyond-the-stereotype/article15410546.ece|title=Beyond the stereotype|date=5 February 2008|publisher=|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref>
==Books== * S. Irfan Habib (ed.). 2018. ''Inqulab: Bhagat Singh on Religion and Revolution ''. New Delhi: Yoda Press, Sage and Select. * S. Irfan Habib (ed.). 2017. ''Indian Nationalism: The Essential Writings''. New Delhi: Aleph. * S. Irfan Habib 2012. ''Jihad or Ijtihad? Religious Orthodoxy and Modern Science in Contemporary Islam''. New Delhi: Harper Collins Publishers India in association with The India Today Group. * S. Irfan Habib and Dhruv. Raina. (eds.). 2007. ''Social History of Science in Colonial India''. New Delhi: Oxford University Press. * S. Irfan Habib. 2007. ''To Make the Deaf Hear: Ideology and Programme of Bhagat Singh and His Comrades''. New Delhi: Three Essays Collective. * Dhruv Raina and S. Irfan Habib. 2004. ''Domesticating Modern Science: A Social History of Science and Culture in Colonial India''. New Delhi: Tulika Books. * Dhruv Raina and S. Irfan Habib (eds.). 1999. ''Situating the History of Science: Dialogues with Joseph Needham''. New Delhi: Oxford University Press.
